---
title: Shrimp, White Bean & Kale Caesar Salad with Broccoli, Garlicky Panko & Toasted Ciabatta Points
description: Our chefs' riff on a vegan Caesar salad is sure to check all the boxes. You’ll pair a base of kale, white beans, and roasted broccoli with a creamy dressing featuring vegan Worcestershire sauce, lemon, mustard, and nutritional yeast—a flavor powerhouse that helps simulate the nutty, cheesy flavor of Parm, minus the dairy. A shower of crispy garlic panko and ciabatta toast points complete the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6862aa8f6c81f96af060381c-6208cfea-06cdf794.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864f1de0203e9f8dbb4c86a-en-US.pdf
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 18 g
  sodium: 2260 mg
time required: 30m
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shrimp-white-bean-and-kale-caesar-salad-6864f1de0203e9f8dbb4c86a
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Remove and discard any
large stems from @kale{4%ounce} if necessary; chop into bite-size pieces. Zest and
quarter @lemon{1%unit}. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and
@black pepper{1%tsp}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly
browned, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Place kale in a #large bowl{}; add a drizzle of @olive oil{large drizzle} and a
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Using your hands, massage (similar to how you would knead
dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #small pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in lemon zest, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the
@nutritional yeast{2%tablespoon}, a pinch of salt, and pepper. Transfer to a
#small bowl{}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon},
@dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, remaining garlic powder, remaining nutritional yeast,
@worcestershire sauce{1/2%tsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Set aside.

> Save any remaining Worcestershire sauce for another use.

Halve @ciabatta{1%unit} and toast until golden brown.

Lightly drizzle cut sides with @olive oil{drizzle}. Halve on a diagonal.

To bowl with kale, add broccoli, beans, and dressing; toss to combine. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salad between plates. Top with toasted panko and as many
@korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with ciabatta points and
remaining lemon wedges on the side.